  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Wherefore now let the fear of the Lord be upon you,.... And act as having that before your eyes, and on your hearts: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "take heed and do it; do the commands enjoined them by him, and do judgment according to the law of God: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for there is no iniquity with the Lord our God; none in his nature, nor in his law; none commanded nor approved of by him, and therefore none should be done by his representatives in judgment: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "nor respect of persons; whether high or low, rich or poor: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "nor taking of gifts; he accepts not the faces of men, nor receives bribes, nor should his judges; this is forbidden by him, Deuteronomy 16:19. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "nor taking of gifts; he accepts not the faces of men, nor receives bribes, nor should his judges; this is forbidden by him, ",
